Card Game: War

//Sequence

Instructions:
1) Divide the deck evenly between 2 people so that each person receives 26 cards. 
2) Each player places their stack of cards face down in front of them.
3) Both players turn up a card at the same time. 
4) The player with the higher card takes both cards and puts them face down on the bottom of their stack.
5) If the cards have the same rank, that means "War" and each player turns up one card face down and one card face up.
6) The player with the higher cards takes both piles. 
7) If the turned up cards are again the same rank, each player places another card face down and turns another card face up. 
8) Player with the highest card takes all 10 cards.
9) Game ends when one player has won all the cards.

//Selection

Divide the deck evenly between two people so that each person receieves 26 cards.

Each player places their stack of cards face down in front of them.

Both players turn up a card at the same time :
    Whoever has the higher card takes both cards and puts them face down on the bottom of their stack.
    If the cards have the same rank, that means "War".
    
In "war", each player turns up one card face down and one card face up. :
    The player with the higher cards take both piles.
    If the turned up cards are again the same rank, each player places another card face down and turns another card face up.
    
Player with the highest card after the previous step takes all 10 cards.   

Game ends when one player has won all the cards.

//Repetition

Divide the deck evenly between two people so that each person receieves 26 cards.

Each player places their stack of cards face down in front of them. Both players turn up a card at the same time.

For both players turn up a card at the same time, :
    Whoever has the higher card takes both cards and puts them face down on the bottom of their stack.
    If the cards have the same rank, that means "War".
    
For "war", each player turns up one card face down and one card face up. :
    The player with the higher cards take both piles.
    If the turned up cards are again the same rank, each player places another card face down and turns another card face up.
    
Player with the highest card after the previous step takes all 10 cards.

Game ends when one player has won all the cards. 
            
